{"word":"ἀγωνιστής","slug":"ἀγωνιστής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγωνιστής</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀγωνίζομαι'><el>ἀγωνίζομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a rival</i> at the games, <i>competitor</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, <el>ἀγ. ἵπποι</el> <i>race</i>- horses, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a debater, opponent</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>one who struggles for a thing</i>, <el>τῆς ἀρετῆς</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}